From: rocky-updater <rocky@sigil.example>
Subject: [PATCH] p3d: cfg-gated tamper injection for divergence demo

Adds a `tamper-demo` cargo feature to sigil-node that, when enabled,
adds +42 SIGIL to wallet [0xDE; 32] during the FIRST block-1 apply.

The tamper is deliberate, signposted, and isolated:
  - Behind #[cfg(feature = "tamper-demo")] so production builds can NEVER
    accidentally ship it (rustc strips the code when feature is off).
  - Logs a loud line on activation so no operator is confused.
  - Single-shot — only fires on block 1, only mutates DEMO_WALLET.

After the tamper applies, the receiver's locally-computed
wallet_state_root won't match the block 1 header's wallet_state_root
(which was computed by the untampered producer). The receiver halts
with exit 78 — proving skill rule #9 (state-root divergence is loud,
not silent).

To use:
  1. Apply this patch to sigil/crates/sigil-node/
  2. Build the tamper variant:
       fluxc build --package sigil-node --release --features tamper-demo
  3. Rename binary so deploy.sh can route it:
       cp target/release/sigil-node releases/v0.0.3/sigil-node-v0.0.3-tamper
  4. Run release.sh's announcement+sign flow against the tamper binary
     (a flag would help — separate task: --variant tamper)

This patch is the smallest possible change that demonstrates divergence
without touching the apply path's correctness in non-tamper builds.

---
NOTE: This is a patch sketch, NOT an applied change. The exact lines
referenced in the diff depend on where rocky's P3-B receiver branch
lands in sigil-node::run_start tick loop. Once P3-B settles, this
patch will need a 5-minute alignment pass before it cleanly applies.

The cfg gate, the constant, the log message, the +42 — all stable.
Only the line numbers and surrounding context will shift.

---

 crates/sigil-node/Cargo.toml          | 6 ++++++
 crates/sigil-node/src/chain.rs        | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 26 insertions(+)

--- a/crates/sigil-node/Cargo.toml
+++ b/crates/sigil-node/Cargo.toml
@@ -X,Y +X,Y @@
 [dependencies]
 # ... existing deps ...

+[features]
+default = []
+# tamper-demo: gated injection point for P3-D divergence demo. NEVER enable
+# in production. Adds +42 SIGIL to DEMO_WALLET on first block-1 apply,
+# producing a deliberate state-root mismatch vs the header. The cfg gate
+# ensures the tamper code is completely absent from default builds.
+tamper-demo = []
+

--- a/crates/sigil-node/src/chain.rs
+++ b/crates/sigil-node/src/chain.rs
@@ -X,Y +X,Y @@
 // inside the function that applies a deserialized block (likely apply_block
 // or run_start's tick loop after drain_events surfaces a TOPIC_BLOCKS message)
+
+    #[cfg(feature = "tamper-demo")]
+    {
+        // P3-D divergence demo: tamper exactly once, on block 1 apply, by
+        // bumping DEMO_WALLET ([0xDE; 32]) by +42 SIGIL BEFORE the block's
+        // own mutations apply. The receiver's wallet_state_root will then
+        // diverge from the producer's header — observable as a loud halt.
+        if block.header.height == 1 {
+            const DEMO_WALLET: [u8; 32] = [0xDE; 32];
+            const SIGIL_TOKEN: [u8; 32] = [0; 32]; // canonical zero = native SIGIL
+            tracing::warn!(
+                target: "tamper-demo",
+                "TAMPER ACTIVE: adding +42 SIGIL to DEMO_WALLET before block 1 apply. \
+                 This binary is for the P3-D divergence demo ONLY — your computed \
+                 wallet_state_root will NOT match the producer's header. Expecting halt."
+            );
+            // Use the chokepoint, not raw map writes — same code path the rest
+            // of the apply takes, so the tamper looks like a legitimate state
+            // change to the SMT but is a divergence vs the producer.
+            let mutation = sigil_state::StateMutation::WalletDelta {
+                wallet: DEMO_WALLET,
+                token: SIGIL_TOKEN,
+                delta: 42,
+            };
+            let tamper_transition = sigil_state::StateTransition {
+                height: block.header.height,
+                mutations: vec![mutation],
+            };
+            let _ = self.state.commit_state_transition(tamper_transition);
+        }
+    }
+
